{"context": "Renewable energy startup Solaris unveiled its floating wind turbine prototype, the Z-500, at a marine expo in Oslo last Friday. The innovative design claims to generate 30% more power than traditional fixed-bottom turbines in deep waters. Founder Lars Jensen demonstrated the model's stability by simulating storm conditions in a large wave tank. Commercial deployment is expected to begin in the North Sea by late 2025. This breakthrough represents a major leap forward in offshore wind technology.", "question": "Where was the Z-500 turbine prototype unveiled?", "answer": "Oslo"}
{"context": "A severe tremor measuring 5.9 on the Richter scale hit the mountainous province of Kumamoto, Japan, late Thursday night, triggering multiple landslides. Local authorities have confirmed at least 28 casualties, primarily due to collapsed traditional homes in rural villages. Prime Minister Fumio Kishida ordered the Self-Defense Forces to assist with rescue operations and supply delivery. Search dogs are currently scanning debris in the town of Mashiki for two reported missing hikers. Neighboring countries have pledged immediate financial aid for reconstruction efforts.", "question": "How many casualties have been confirmed following the tremor?", "answer": "28"}
{"context": "The Boston Celtics clinched a thrilling 108-105 victory over the Miami Heat in the NBA Eastern Conference finals at TD Garden. Veteran guard Jayson Tatum hit the decisive three-pointer with just 12 seconds remaining on the clock. Head coach Joe Mazzulla commended the squad's defensive intensity after trailing by 15 points in the third quarter. A sold-out crowd of 19,156 fans witnessed the comeback, marking the highest attendance of the playoffs. The win secures Boston's place in the upcoming Finals series.", "question": "Who made the decisive three-pointer for the Boston Celtics?", "answer": "Jayson Tatum"}
{"context": "Governor Robert Chen declared his intention to run for the Senate seat in the next federal election during a town hall in Austin on Wednesday. His campaign priorities include expanding broadband access to rural areas and reforming healthcare costs. This declaration follows weeks of rumors about his challenge to the current seat holder. Chen previously served as the Mayor of Austin for three terms before becoming Governor. Recent surveys indicate he has a slight advantage over his primary opponents in urban districts.", "question": "Where did Governor Chen announce his Senate run?", "answer": "Austin"}
{"context": "Fashion retailer GreenThread launched a new collection of clothes dyed using algae-based pigments that require no fresh water. The project, named 'Verde Wave,' intends to save 2 million gallons of water annually by 2027. Pop-up stores will open concurrently in Paris, Milan, and Seoul starting next Monday. For every garment purchased, the company will plant five mangrove trees in coastal regions. Sustainability advocates have welcomed the innovation as a crucial shift for the textile industry.", "question": "What is the name of the new water-saving project?", "answer": "Verde Wave"}
{"context": "Devastating mudslides in the Andes Mountains have isolated over 8,500 villagers in northern Peru this month. Heavy seasonal rains saturated the soil, causing slopes to give way and block major highways. The military has deployed helicopters to drop food rations and medicine to communities cut off near Trujillo. Mining engineers estimate that access to two major copper deposits will be restricted for at least six weeks. Emergency tents and hygiene kits are being distributed to families living in temporary camps.", "question": "How many villagers have been isolated by the mudslides?", "answer": "8,500"}
{"context": "Drone delivery firm SkyRoute announced a milestone of 1 million successful autonomous deliveries across its network in Asia. The growth was fueled by the introduction of their lightweight Drone-X model capable of carrying heavier payloads. Founder Li Wei credited the achievement to improved battery life and relaxed aviation regulations in Southeast Asia. Distribution centers in Singapore and Bangkok are now operating at maximum capacity to handle holiday demand. Logistics rivals have acknowledged SkyRoute's efficiency in last-mile delivery solutions.", "question": "How many autonomous deliveries has SkyRoute completed?", "answer": "1 million"}
{"context": "The International Atomic Energy Agency confirmed the safe decommissioning of the老旧 nuclear reactor in Kashiwazaki, Japan, on Thursday. Director General Rafael Mariano Grossi highlighted the successful removal of spent fuel rods without any radiation leaks. Decommissioning teams achieved 95% completion of the primary containment vessel cleanup ahead of schedule. Although the site is cleared, long-term monitoring of groundwater will continue for another decade. Officials from 12 nations observed the final phase as a model for future reactor closures.", "question": "Who highlighted the successful removal of spent fuel rods?", "answer": "Rafael Mariano Grossi"}
{"context": "A sophisticated phishing campaign compromised the email servers of four leading US healthcare providers early Monday morning. The attack disrupted appointment scheduling systems for approximately 2 million patients in California, Texas, and New York. Cybersecurity firm NetGuard traced the intrusion to a hacker collective identified as 'Crimson Tide.' While no medical records were exfiltrated, internal communication logs were temporarily locked. The hospitals are collaborating with the FBI to trace the attackers and reinforce firewall defenses.", "question": "What is the name of the hacker collective behind the phishing campaign?", "answer": "Crimson Tide"}
{"context": "The European Space Agency successfully launched the Euclid telescope from Kourou, French Guiana, tasked with mapping the dark universe. Project lead Dr. Elena Rossi and engineer Marc Dubois monitored the Ariane 6 rocket during its precise insertion into orbit. The mission aims to create a 3D map of billions of galaxies over the next six years. Hundreds of scientists gathered at the control center to celebrate the flawless launch sequence. This mission marks a new era in understanding the composition of dark matter and dark energy.", "question": "From where was the Euclid telescope launched?", "answer": "Kourou, French Guiana"}
{"context": "The municipality of Seattle passed a progressive traffic congestion tax that charges vehicles entering the downtown core during peak hours. Councilwoman Sarah Kim argued the revenue is vital for expanding the city's light rail network. Critics plan to challenge the measure in court, arguing it disproportionately affects low-income commuters. The tax scheme is scheduled to begin enforcement on March 15th, pending administrative finalization. Public transit unions endorsed the policy as a necessary step toward reducing carbon emissions.", "question": "When is the new traffic congestion tax scheduled to begin?", "answer": "March 15th"}
{"context": "Golfer Rory McIlroy edged out Scottie Scheffler in a playoff at the Masters Tournament at Augusta National. The duel extended to the second extra hole, finishing with a par save that secured the green jacket. McIlroy completes his career Grand Slam, becoming only the sixth player to achieve this feat in the modern era. The winner's share of the purse was $3.6 million, setting a new record for golf tournaments. Spectators at the 18th green erupted in cheers that echoed across the course.", "question": "How many holes did the playoff at the Masters last?", "answer": "two"}
{"context": "An unprecedented heatwave gripped the Iberian Peninsula, pushing temperatures to 47 degrees Celsius and sparking numerous brush fires. Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez declared a national emergency to mobilize water resources for agriculture in Andalusia. Thermometers in Seville broke historical records, posing severe health risks to the elderly population. Tourism boards reported a sudden drop in visitors, while local pools remained open 24 hours to provide relief. Utility companies are struggling to meet the surge in electricity demand for air conditioning.", "question": "What temperature did the heatwave reach in the region?", "answer": "47 degrees Celsius"}
{"context": "Biotech firm GeneHeal obtained emergency authorization from the EMA for its groundbreaking gene therapy, CureSickle. Patient data from Phase 3 trials indicated a 90% elimination of painful crisis episodes in subjects with sickle cell disease. The therapy will be administered in specialized clinics across Europe starting in October, priced at €1.8 million per treatment. Dr. Hans Mueller, the chief scientist, described the authorization as a 'new dawn for genetic medicine.' National health systems are negotiating bulk purchase agreements to ensure accessibility.", "question": "What percentage of painful crisis episodes did CureSickle eliminate in trials?", "answer": "90%"}
{"context": "The BRICS summit ended in Johannesburg with participating countries agreeing to a new common currency framework for trade. Members pledged to reduce reliance on the US dollar by 40% in bilateral transactions by 2030. South African President Cyril Ramaphosa chaired the summit, focusing on infrastructure development loans for member states. The agreement outlines a roadmap for establishing a joint payment system to bypass SWIFT restrictions. Economic analysts remain skeptical about the timeline but acknowledge the geopolitical shift.", "question": "By what year do BRICS nations aim to reduce dollar reliance by 40%?", "answer": "2030"}
{"context": "A collision between a cargo ship and a fishing trawler occurred off the coast of Busan, South Korea, on Sunday afternoon. Roughly 15 crew members from the trawler were rescued by coast guard helicopters, while three remain missing. Maritime police have cordoned off the area to prevent oil spills from damaging the nearby marine sanctuary. The Korea Maritime Safety Tribunal has launched an inquiry into the navigation errors that led to the incident. Nearby ports have suspended operations until the wreckage is cleared from the shipping lane.", "question": "How many crew members were rescued from the trawler?", "answer": "15"}
{"context": "Social media giant ConnectUp revealed plans to acquire messaging app ChatBubble in a transaction worth $28 billion. The merged platform would dominate the instant messaging sector with over 60% market share, prompting scrutiny from EU commissioners. ConnectUp CEO Sophie Laurent claimed the acquisition would enhance end-to-end encryption standards for all users. Data migration for ChatBubble's user base is expected to take 12 months with zero service interruption. Rival apps like Signal and Telegram saw a spike in new registrations after the announcement.", "question": "What is the total value of the ConnectUp and ChatBubble acquisition?", "answer": "$28 billion"}
{"context": "Torrential rains in central India have submerged over 35,000 acres of cotton farmland in the state of Maharashtra. Monsoon floods overwhelmed local drainage systems, drowning crops and stranding livestock in higher districts. Relief workers from the National Disaster Response Force are distributing dry rations to farmers in the Vidarbha region. Agricultural departments estimate that cotton yields for the season could drop by 25% due to the waterlogging. Veterinary teams are vaccinating cattle against waterborne diseases in the affected zones.", "question": "How many acres of cotton farmland have been submerged?", "answer": "35,000"}
{"context": "The Bank of England raised its base rate by half a percentage point to tackle inflation persisting near 4%. Governor Andrew Bailey warned that additional tightening could occur if wage growth remains unchecked. Fixed-rate mortgage deals soared to 6.8%, causing a sharp decline in property viewing appointments. Financial experts suggest this hike will dampen business investment but strengthen the pound's value globally. The Monetary Policy Committee will reconvene in November to assess the latest economic indicators.", "question": "To what level did fixed-rate mortgage deals rise after the announcement?", "answer": "6.8%"}
{"context": "Celebrated chef Massimo Bottura opened his innovative fusion restaurant 'Root & Sea' in Melbourne this weekend. The menu features indigenous Australian ingredients paired with traditional Italian cooking techniques. Reservations for the first month were fully booked within 48 hours, surpassing 5,000 requests. Bottura plans to host a culinary masterclass series in Sydney and Brisbane before returning to Italy. Food critics are already predicting the venue will earn three Michelin stars within its first year.", "question": "How many reservation requests did 'Root & Sea' receive for the first month?", "answer": "5,000"}
